<p class="">I will tell the right hon. Gentleman, if he will not be so impatient. I am stating that War Office policy as stated to the United States was, "We will standardise on ·280 inch." Whether or not the right hon. Gentleman knew I do not know, but he cannot have it both ways. He was Minister of Defence; he ought to have known. The right hon. Member for Dundee, West was Secretary of State for War, so I presume that he did know.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
